name: Archery Paralympics
summary: These headlines highlight the remarkable achievements of Paralympic athletes in archery. Matt Stutzman, an armless archer, is replicating the adrenaline of competition through heart-pumping activities to prepare for the 2024 Paris Olympics. Matt Stutzman is not the only armless archer, as others have followed in his footsteps. Army veteran Tabansky has triumphed over the world's top archer to claim Paralympic gold. Oznur Cure Girdi has earned Paralympic gold with an exceptional performance. Day 3 of the 2024 Paris Olympics will offer a thrilling lineup of archery, shooting, and taekwondo competitions. Indian archer Sheetal Devi, who lacks arms, is aspiring for Paralympic gold. British archer Jodie Grinham has juggled competition with motherhood and pregnancy, winning Paralympic bronze while pregnant. The schedule for the 2024 Paralympics includes daily TV coverage and online streaming options. Yuya Oe, a "power dad," has found success in archery despite his physical challenges.

summary: 49ers receiver Ricky Pearsall was shot in the chest during an attempted robbery in San Francisco's Union Square. According to the San Francisco Police Department, the suspect approached Pearsall and demanded his belongings, and when Pearsall resisted, the suspect shot him. The suspect fled the scene and remains at large. The 49ers released a statement expressing their support for Pearsall and condemning the violence.
